 All measurements were carried out in low vacuum, less than 1 mTorr, in
 a Model 6000 Physical Properties Measurement System (PPMS, Quantum Design).
 A Keithley 6340 was used as the current and voltage bias source as well
 as the corresponding two-point voltage and current measurements, two Keithley
 2182A were used for four-point and hall measurements across the voltage
 leads, and a Keithley 2400 was used to provide the gate voltage bias.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Optical crystal measurements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Indium and selenium can form a variety of compounds, and the growth process
 is complicated and may result in crystals with mixed polymorphs, see section
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:In-Se-compounds"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "liu2019atomically"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 Because of this, several optical measurements were used to confirm the
 stoichiometry and lattice stacking of the material used in our devices.
 X-Ray diffraction measurements displayed peaks corresponding to the 
\begin_inset Formula $R3m$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $R\bar{3}m$
\end_inset

 space groups, indicating 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

- or 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

-phase.
 Raman showed peaks near 104, 179, and 193 
\begin_inset Formula $cm^{-1}$
\end_inset

corresponding to the 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{1}^{\,1}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $E^{3}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{1}^{\,4}$
\end_inset

 peaks of 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{\ensuremath{\alpha}-In}_{2}\textrm{Se}_{3}$
